# Expert Profile: Ashley Lewin (Demand Gen & Proprietary Data)

**Core Thesis:** In the age of commodity AI content, **Proprietary Data** is the only true differentiator. Use original research as a "Core Asset" to fuel a "Launch One, Distribute a Million" content engine.

---

## 1. The "Proprietary Data" Moat
Ashley argues that B2B brands must move away from generic advice and toward data-backed authority.
* **Original Research:** Conducting surveys or using internal product data to create industry benchmarks.
* **AI Search Optimization:** Research-backed content is prioritized by AI-driven search engines (AEO) that look for unique, non-derivative facts.
* **The Efficiency Loop:** One major research report can be "whipped up" into 20+ pieces of content, reducing the time spent brainstorming new topics.

## 2. Content Atomization for Strategic Demand Gen

| Core Research Asset | Social Derivative | Business Outcome |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Industry Benchmarks** | LinkedIn Polls & Carousels | High engagement & authority |
| **Vertical Playbooks** | Niche-targeted text posts | High-intent inbound leads |
| **Expert Webinars** | Video snippets & quote cards | Educational trust building |
| **Customer Success Data** | Narrative case studies | Accelerated deal cycles |



## 3. The "Website as Salesperson" Strategy
LinkedIn serves as the "megaphones," but the website must be the "storefront" that closes the deal.
* **Intent-Driven Traffic:** Organic social should drive traffic to specific, user-friendly conversion points (e.g., calculators, teardowns, or free tools).
* **Storefront Ownership:** Treat the website as your top-performing salesperson. Ensure it is optimized for high-intent buyers who are ready to act.
* **Algorithmic Insurance:** By focusing on driving traffic to an "owned" site, you protect your pipeline from sudden social media algorithm changes.

